==English==
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/heɪl/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪl|-eɪl]]

===Etymology 1===
From Old Norse [[heill]] ‘health, prosperity’.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|-}}

# [[health|Health]], [[welfare]].

===Etymology 2===
Representing a Northern dialectal form of Old English [[hal#Old English|hāl]] ‘whole’.  Compare [[whole]], [[hail]] (adjective).

====Adjective====
{{en-adj|hal|er}}

#[[sound|Sound]], [[entire]], [[healthy]]; [[robust]], not impaired.

===Etymology 3===
From Old (and modern) French [[haler]], from Old Norse [[hala]], from Germanic.  Compare [[haul]].

====Verb====
{{en-verb|hal|ing}}

# To [[drag]], [[pull]], especially forcibly.

